<l:introbody><l:h1>Scenario 1, August 1914 - April 1917.<l:/h1>
The shape of the future world after August 1914 will now be decided by force and the strategic wisdom of the Central powers and the Triple Entente. Casualties on both sides will be high in the following many months of war. The Germans are preparing an offensive move on the western front into Belgium and France. On the eastern front the German forces are weaker as they hope to make a fast invation in france and then turn against the Russian force. But the Russian army is ready to invade East Prussia and stands strong at the border of Turkie. Austria-Hungaria is preparing the invation of the southern Russia and Serbia. In Serbia they have a personal vendeta to settle, the murder in Sarajevo. Thus prepared to invade Greece, Turkie is caught between the Russian and African armies. 
<l:h1>The war has begun...<l:/h1>
